The answer to me is simple, We all shared a common bond, a unity and trust unmatched in corporate America or by any other experience since that time. Its that friendship, trust and unity that can never again be duplicated.<br><br>
That common bond that only war breeds, its called brotherhood, love, honor, pride, peace, joy, laughter, fear, humility and bravery it is all this and it is all intermingled and everlasting. It can only be enjoyed, understood and supported by those that suffered as well as enjoyed similar circumstances.<br>

